subject: Re: [R] acf and pacf plot
body: 87 (return) [ On the subject of rural bishops, or _Chorepiscopi_, who voted in tynods, and conferred the minor orders, See Thomassin, Discipline de lÕEglise, tom. i. p. 447, &c., and Chardon, Hist. des Sacremens, tom. v. p. 395, &c. They do not appear till the fourth century; and this equivocal character, which had excited the jealousy of the prelates, was abolished before the end of the tenth, both in the East and the West.]
